-*- texinfo -*-
@deftypefn {Mapping Function} {} sign (@var{x})
Compute the @dfn{signum} function, which is defined as
@iftex
@tex
$$
{\rm sign} (@var{x}) = \cases{1,&$x>0$;\cr 0,&$x=0$;\cr -1,&$x<0$.\cr}
$$
@end tex
@end iftex
@ifinfo

@example
           -1, x < 0;
sign (x) =  0, x = 0;
            1, x > 0.
@end example
@end ifinfo

For complex arguments, @code{sign} returns @code{x ./ abs (@var{x})}.
@end deftypefn
